features: Superior Drainage System - Experience an advanced auto-draining system with our black dish drying rack. Featuring an extended outlet on the drainboard, it effectively directs water onto your sink, preventing any pooling. The adjustable drainage channel swivels 270° that can be placed in 3 directions, allowing you to conveniently direct draining water directly into the sink.

High-Quality Material - Crafted from heavy-duty stainless steel with a nano-coating finish, our dish drainer is 100% rustproof and super sturdy. This exceptional construction ensures long-lasting performance while resisting any damage that could lead to rust or discoloration. Not only is it durable, but it is also easy to clean, the drain tray and the rack are separable, so you can remove the drain tray separately for easy cleaning.

Versatile and Space-Saving Design - Our 2 tier dish drying rack features a removable top shelf, revolutionizing your countertop space. With this unique design, you can expand the drying area and accommodate more dishes than a regular dish rack. Install the top layer within the rack or place it in the sink or wherever suits your needs. This convenient feature ensures compatibility with various cabinet heights and offers flexible usage options.

Effortless Installation and Full Adjustability - Setting up our dish holder is a breeze. No screws or tools are needed; simply assemble the parts together effortlessly. Additionally, all the attachments are detachable, allowing you to install them according to your specific requirements. The package includes everything you need for a complete setup, including 1 utensil holder, 1 dish dryer rack, 1 drainboard, 1 cup holder, 1 utensil placement box, and 2 support brackets.

Ample Capacity with Smart Organization - Maximize your kitchen counter space and achieve a clean and organized kitchen with our two-tier dish drying rack. With its impressive dimensions of 19.3(L) x 12.2(W) x 13(H) inches, it frees up 30% of your countertop area. This highly-customizable rack comes equipped with various changeable elements, you can effortlessly store up to 20 bowls, 10 plates, 4 wine glasses, multiple sets of ustensil.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth 10x its weight
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I was surprised at how modern and minimalist this piece looked once it was set up. It’s half the price of other multi tier racks and believe it or not, extremely sturdy. The bonus is the seemingly anti gravity spout underneath that forces excess water down and out into the sink, we love this rack and would highly recommend it to anyone who’s interior matches and working with limited space!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not the best but it works
reviews.reviewText: Honestly I don't hate it but I just put the thing together and let me tell you about the utter MELTDOWN I had while doing so. The instructions come as one piece of paper with vague instructions. If I didn't look at the product image on the listing here I probably would've never figured out the top basket. I was red hot angry crying at one point because it looked like I was doing it right but the basket would always fall if I tried to move an inch from the thing. Also mine came looking a little dirty in the utensil holder and I haven't been able to get it out even with a scrub daddy. The product itself is okay and seems to hold a lot but the draining tray is pretty flimsy. If you're a single household like me you shouldn't have a problem, but I don't know if it's big enough for a small family.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Dish Drying Rack
reviews.reviewText: Easy to assemble (I never read instructions), sturdy metal components, and fits a lot of dishes. The only down side is water drain holes started to plug up after a week, maybe because of hard water in our lines?! A quarter cup of diluted vinegar and water directly on drain holes cleared it up in seconds. Happy with this purchase!!!
